entry.title: Ukraine's Zelensky Warns Against Trial of Azovstal Prisoners
entry.content: The leader of a Russian-backed breakaway region announced details of plans to put Ukrainian soldiers on trial, a move that President Zelensky warned would mean an end to negotiations between Kyiv and Moscow.

entry.title: Ousted Pakistan Prime Minister Imran Khan Faces Arrest on Terror Charge
entry.content: The arrest threat intensifies the showdown between the former leader and the country’s current government and powerful military.

entry.title: Crimea, Once a Bastion of Russian Power, Now Reveals Its Weakness
entry.content: The strikes deep inside the Russian-occupied territory have disrupted Moscow’s plans to drive further into southern Ukraine and potentially forced a rethink of its broader strategy, military analysts and officials said.
